<br>
When I got the elaborate scimitar, I lost 9 raw AC by putting away my paw...no AC on epic, either. On the other side, I gain 11 WIS (elaborate is 9, epic is 20), and my current wis is exactly 200. <br>
<br>
Some of my other gear is crap, so don't laugh :p<br>
<br>
Some ideas I have come up with: <br>
<br>
Replace plat jasper rings with velium fire opal (-12 wis for +12AC and +130 HP)<br>
<br>
Replace shroud of nature with treeweave (-6 wis for +12 AC, but also -8 FR and CR). I would have loved to already had a Verm tunic, but I've never even seen one drop. <br>
<br>
Replace RyGorr Oracle Shield with SBS (-5 wis and 50 mana for +13 AC) actually, I'd love to do that, but I really can't afford it. SBS is just too expensive for me. <br>
<br>
I can also add more wis at the cost of a little AC...I have a prayer shawl that isn't being used, and am currently using an obulus death shroud. This would increase my wis by 5 while lowering my AC by 5. I would need to get more AC to make up for it, but it would also give me more wis to play with. I would then have 216 wis. <br>
<br>
I really hate selling any of it, because 1) I hate selling, and 2) I like to have the stuff around so I can manuever it, to get the stats I'm looking for. I also have the 46 cleric I am looking out for, too, although getting wis has not really been very difficult, especially when I start going to Hate. Anything I sell, I cut off an option. <br>
<br>
I can get the treeweave for just a few hours time. <br>
<br>
I am also considering looking for new guants, since with the epic, I'll have snare from an item..thoughts on that? For example, just how long is the cast time for the epic effect?<br>
<br>
I'm looking for opinions on all that, and other suggestions I hadn't thought of. <br>
<br>
<br>
