<br>
I *still* keep Ensnare loaded, although it definitely isn't really needed. <br>
<br>
With the epic, you're going to have 211 Wisdom, so you'll want to try and get as close to 200 as you can. You already state some pretty good alternatives. I think it's oretty important to also look at the circumstances in which you play... for instance, as a raid druid, I tend to concentrate on hp, mana and resists after the 200 wisdom barrier is reached. <br>
<br>
Since it appears to me your primary concern is AC, I would<br>
<br>
1. Replace your SoN with a Treeweave. (-6WIS, -8FR/CR, +12AC) This brings you down to 205 WIS. <br>
<br>
2. Replace 1 Platinum Jasper Ring with a Velium Jasper Ring (+1 WIS)  This brings you up to 206 WIS. <br>
<br>
3. Replace the other Platinum Jasper Ring with 1 Vel. Fire Opal Ring. (-6WIS, +6AC, +65HP)<br>
<br>
This gets you 200 Wisdom and raises your raw AC by 18, and your HP by 65. However, you lose 8CR/FR from the Shroud. This is probably one of the best possible results.<br>
<br>
Alternatively, you could also replace the remaining Plat Jasper with a Vel. Jade Ring (+5AC, +30hp, +30mana).<br>
<br>
This would keep your goal of 200 WIS, but only net you a raw AC of 17, hp +30 and mana +30. Again, you lose the 8FR/8CR.<br>
<br>
Another alternative would be<br>
<br>
Diamond Wedding Ring (+2AC, +3 DEX, +5 WIS, +5 INT, +15 MANA, +8FR, +8CR). <br>
<br>
Basically, this ring would make up for the bonuses lost via the Shroud of Nature. If you go with this alternative, I highly recommend you replace the Obulous Death Shroud with a Tattered Mantle. (Yes, odd choice, I know)<br>
<br>
The net result would be 202 Wisdom, +14AC, +15 MANA, +20 HP, no change in your FR/CR.<br>
<br>
In any case, all of these will make up for the lost AC of the Paw...<br>
