<br>
for gloves, something very easy to get is cured tizmak.  you would retain the 9 ac of ES, but add 8 svf and 8 svc.  more than an adequate swap.<br>
<br>
the jasper rings definately need to go, replaced by either the vel jade or vel fire.  you can also do the coldain ring quest up to lvl 8 with only one group needed on occassion, and that is a very very good ring.  replacing your rings with the vel jade means you can also drop the SoN for a treeweave if you dont mind losing the resists without dropping your mana pool much at all (swapping 6 wis SoN for 60 mana rings), and the resists would be negated if you added the tizmak gloves.<br>
<br>
total change from SoN, ES gloves, plat jasper rings to treeweave, cured tizmak gloves, vel jade rings: +22 ac, +10 str, +60 hp, +60 mana at a wis total of 193 with epic (which will also add 90 mana, 10 hp, 10 str, 10 svall).  cost would only be about 1kp for the vel jade rings, as the treeweave and gloves you could get solo.<br>
<br>
i'm really big on resists, so i myself would probably keep the SoN and get the tizmak gloves and vel jade rings.  people place way too much importance on maintaining a 200 wis.  there is no magic wis number you have to keep, and if you can swap out wis for a better item with nearly equivalent mana, then do it.  also depends on your game.  at the high end, resists are what save your life, not any amount of ac.  a dragon who hits for 500 will still hit for 500 if you have 900 ac instead of 860, but their AE may not hit if you have resist of 150 instead of 100. <p>-K<br>
